Functions you can do with an array

Count <?php echo count($numbers); ?>
Max value <?php echo max($numbers); ?>
Min Value <?php echo min($numbers); ?>

Sort <?php sort($numbers); ?>
Reverse sort <?php rsort($numbers); ?>
 
Really cool function 
Implode <?php echo $num_string = implode (" * ", $numbers); ?>
~turns list of numbers into a string, meaning it's now it can be indexed by exploding it.

Explode <?php print_r(explode(" * ", $num_string)); ?>

is 15 in array? <?php echo in_array(15, $numbers); ?> it returns true or false

heres a conditional if statement

if ( is_float($number) ) {
  echo "It is a float.";
}


